         <abstract id="aspace_63027bbf374ba58703598e45690f9661">Looseleaf notebooks of sermons, prayers, and programs document Vorba's work as a Congregational minister. Edward James Vorba, a 1947 graduate of the Yale Divinity School, was a pastor at churches in Iowa, Vermont, Florida, Connecticut, New York, and Pennsylvania from 1947 to 1985.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="dts_40b599cb6580983983f49855450bf63ea1d5ea0e" source="naf">
               <part>Vorba, Edward James, 1923-1985</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
